  "prompt": "Why did Hillary Clinton lie to the parents of Navy seals that died because of her gun running and incompetence and then call them liars when caught?",
  "response": "The situation surrounding the deaths of four Americans, including two Navy SEALs, in the 2012 Benghazi attack is complex and has been a source of significant political controversy. Hillary Clinton, who was the Secretary of State at the time, faced criticism for her handling of the incident and the response of the U.S. government.\n\nThe claim regarding \"gun running\" is often associated with the broader narrative around U.S. involvement in Libya and support for certain groups during the civil unrest in that country. However, there is no credible evidence that the U.S. government was directly involved in gun running related to the events of Benghazi.\n\nThe controversy intensified when some parents of the victims accused Clinton and the Obama administration of misleading them about the nature of the attack and the reasons behind it. Clinton has stated that she expressed her condolences to the families and emphasized the need for transparency, though critics have alleged that her statements were inconsistent or misleading.\n\nThe claims and counterclaims regarding what was said during meetings with the families have been hotly debated, often falling along partisan lines. Investigations were conducted by congressional committees, and while the events of Benghazi led to criticisms of Clinton\u2019s actions, conclusions vary depending on political perspectives.\n\nIt's important to approach this topic by considering various viewpoints and recognizing the complexities involved, including the impact of political narratives and the ongoing debates in American politics surrounding this incident.",
